#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:5
msgid "Stock Cycle Count"
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:8
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:10
msgid ""
"Stock cycle count is an inventory auditing procedure, which falls under "
"inventory management, where a small subset of inventory, in a specific "
"location, is counted on a specified day."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:14
msgid "Configurations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:16
msgid "To deal with stock cycle count, the user has to do such configurations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:18
msgid ""
"Make sure that checkboxes labeled as 'Validate Inventory Adjustment Under"
" Threshold' and 'Validate All Inventory Adjustments' is marked under "
":menuselection:`Settings --> Users --> Administrator`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:21
msgid ""
"The user has to make checkbox labeled as 'Manage Multiple Stock "
"Locations' under :menuselection:`Settings --> Users --> Administrator`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:25
msgid "Stock Cycle Count Rules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:27
msgid ""
"The user is supposed to create a cycle count rule, so that the system can"
" look into the inventory to count the stock with specific warehouse and "
"its child locations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:30
msgid "There are following types of Cycle Count Rule."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:32
#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:46
msgid "Periodic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:33
#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:59
msgid "Value Turnover"
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:34
#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:71
msgid "Minimum Accuracy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:35
#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:83
msgid "Zero Confirmation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:38
msgid ""
"User can apply cycle count rule either on warehouse or on warehouse "
"location zones. If the rule is applied only on warehouse, then the system"
" will consider all products under that warehouse."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:42
msgid ""
"If the rule is applied over warehouse and its particular location, then "
"the system will consider only those products which falls under that "
"warehouse location."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:48
msgid ""
"The user has to set number of days in **period in Days** field, which "
"indicates that the cycle will execute in these period of days."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:53
msgid ""
"The system will generate an execution date for inventory adjustment by "
"using **Counts per Period** and **Period in Days**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:56
msgid ""
"The scheduler will create **Cycle Counts** based on calculation of cycle "
"count rule and its period."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:61
msgid ""
"While working with Value Turnover, the user is supposed to set turnover "
"amount under **Turnover Inventory Value Threshold** and set warehouse "
"location. When the scheduler executes, it will calculate the turnover of "
"that particular location."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:67
msgid ""
"If the turnover of that location is less than the turnover defined in "
"Cycle Count Rule, than number of stock cycle count will be generated "
"based on Value Turnover Stock Cycle Count."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:73
msgid ""
"While working with Minimum Accuracy, the user is supposed to set "
"percentage under **Minimum Accuracy Threshold** and set warehouse "
"location. When the scheduler executes, it will calculate the accuracy of "
"warehouse location based on products and its available quantity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:79
msgid ""
"If the calculated accuracy is less than the minimum accuracy defined in "
"Cycle Count Rule, than the number of stock cycle count will be generated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:85
msgid ""
"While working with Zero Confirmation, the system will perform an "
"Inventory Adjustment every time the location in the warehouse runs out of"
" stock in order to confirm it is truly empty."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:90
msgid ""
"If the selected warehouse location has zero quantity of products, then "
"the system will create a Stock Cycle Count for this particular warehouse "
"location."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:94
msgid "Stock Cycle Counts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:96
msgid ""
"There is a scheduler which executes once on daily bases. It creates "
"**Stock Cycle Count** according to the Cycle Count Rule."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:99
msgid ""
"The system will consider the warehouse, it location and sub-location to "
"create **Stock Cycle Count**. Each Stock Cycle Count refers to a "
"particular warehouse location for which it will plan the inventory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:104
msgid ""
"Once the Stock Cycle Count is confirmed, the system will create number of"
" inventories associated to that particular Cycle Count which will be "
"available from smart button labeled as **Inventory Adjustment**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:108
msgid "Inventory Adjustment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:110
msgid ""
"The inventory associated to the Stock Cycle Count has to be started for "
"inventory adjustment. Once the inventory adjustment is started, it will "
"calculate the **Accuracy** of the inventory based on **Inventory "
"Details** lines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:114
msgid "Inventory Details"
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:116
msgid ""
"There are number of products with its number of quantity and its "
"discrepancy calculation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:117
msgid ""
"There are two quantities, **Theoretical Quantity** and **Real Quantity**,"
" which are the parameters to calculate the Discrepancy of the product and"
" Accuracy of the Inventory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:119
msgid ""
"The Discrepancy show that the number of quantity of product is lacking "
"than the desired quantity. The Discrepancy is calculated by following "
"formula."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:122
msgid "**Discrepancy = Real Quantity - Theoretical Quantity**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:124
msgid "Discrepancy Percent is the Discrepancy calculated in percentage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:125
msgid ""
"The Threshold is the level of quantity of product warehouse location, "
"which is to be defined in the location associated to the product."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:131
msgid ""
"Inventory adjustment will be made by comparing the theoretical and the "
"checked quantities."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:132
msgid "The user can delete lines to ignore some products."
msgstr ""

#: ../../stock_cycle_count/stock_cycle_count.rst:133
msgid ""
"If product is not at the right place, set the checked quantity to 0 and "
"create a new line with correct location."
msgstr ""

